					<p>
	We just released Wygwam 3.2, a humble update with a bug fix, better Assets support, and some handy new extension hooks.
</p>
<!--pagebreak-->
<p>
	The new extensions hooks make it possible for other add-ons to add new toolbar buttons to Wygwam’s toolbar configurator. That gives users the power to choose which Wygwam configurations should get the new toolbar buttons, and where they should be placed. We’ve even written a <a href="http://docs.pixelandtonic.com/wygwam/developers/ckeditor_plugins.html" target="_blank">tutorial</a> that outlines how to do it.
</p>
<p>
	Read the full release notes in <a href="http://docs.pixelandtonic.com/wygwam/changelog.html#wygwam-3-2" target="_blank">the documentation</a>, and get the update over at <a href="https://devot-ee.com/add-ons/wygwam" target="_blank">Devot:ee</a>.
</p>
