					<p>
	Hot on the heels of <a href="/blog/wygwam-3">Wygwam 3</a>, we’ve just released a little update to <a href="http://devot-ee.com/add-ons/field-pack" target="_blank">Field Pack</a> which adds <a href="http://www.krea.com/content-elements" target="_blank">Content Elements</a> compatibility to each of the seven bundled fieldtypes!
</p>
<!--pagebreak-->
<p>
	To recap, Content Elements is an EE fieldtype that lets you create editorial composed of different types of content (text, images, code samples, etc.) in no particular order.
</p>
<p>
	    Coupled with <a href="http://devot-ee.com/add-ons/stash" target="_blank">Stash</a>, we expect people are going to find some pretty interesting use cases for Field Pack + Content Elements. For example, Switch or Pill might be used to define the placement of the following Wygwam element.
</p>
<p>
	    We can’t wait to see how you take advantage of it!
</p>
