					<p>
	        Ever since launching Pixel &amp; Tonic, I’ve thought about adding a consulting arm to the business. There are a few reasons for that, but the main one is that I think it’s important for us to be at the other end of our software from time to time.
</p>
<!--pagebreak-->
<p>
	 As a software company, we’ve been so focused on building our software that we’ve only had a couple opportunities to actually <strong>use</strong> the things, working on our own websites. That needs to change.
</p>
<p>
	        They say that you can always tell when software is actually used by its developers, and I believe it. The difference is in the details. Clever little touches here and there, that reveal the creator’s love for their product.
</p>
<p>
	        Now that Craft 1.0 is out, I felt that now is the time to give it a shot. So as of today, we are officially taking requests. If you have a project that could use a little help in our areas of expertise, please do <a href="/consulting">get in touch</a>!
</p>
